	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 14th 6:30 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>Yes check out eqtraders.com tailoring sections extensively before you try this.  All the "good" velious tailoring armor trivial past the 250 skill cap.  JC also has this problem with its high end jewelry, but the difference is how easy it is to raise skill.  JC just takes some pp and a few hours.  Tailoring requires maniacal effort to even hit 200.<br><br>Once you top out Wu's Armor at 162 (or if you are halfling, cultural tailoring around 170 or 180 something), the next items you can make trivial at 232-250+.  Add in that from skill 1 to skill 250, there are NO tailoring recipes where all ingredients come from vendors.  Every tailoring recipe involves farming mobs for dropped items...<br><br>And on the high skill tailoring items, you often need drops from fairly high level mobs that not everyone kills (very time consuming, some require groups, at the least very expensive to buy from others), mana vials made by enchanters (time consuming and very expensive even if you are an enchanter yourself), as well as foraged and smithed items.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
